    <title>Hi-Fi Rush studio saved from Microsoft shutdown</title>
    <content type="html">  

    &lt;figure&gt;
      &lt;img alt="A screenshot from the video game Hi-Fi Rush." src="https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3NQpa2E_kG71bJjBlY-misM6HQU=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73515730/the_making_of_hi_fi_rush_8.0.jpg" /&gt;
        &lt;figcaption&gt;Image: Tango Gameworks&lt;/figcaption&gt;
    &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;p id="NmQbW7"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hi-Fi Rush&lt;/em&gt; developer Tango Gameworks has been spared closure, three months after Microsoft announced plans to shut down the studio. Krafton, the South Korean publisher behind &lt;em&gt;PUBG: Battlegrounds&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;The Callisto Protocol,&lt;/em&gt; &lt;a href="https://press.krafton.com/en-US/KRAFTON-Strengthens-Global-Presence-Through-Strategic-Integration-of-T"&gt;announced on Monday&lt;/a&gt; that it had acquired the game and its Japanese studio, and is working with Xbox to enable a “smooth transition” to ensure the Tango Gameworks team can “continue developing the &lt;em&gt;Hi-Fi Rush&lt;/em&gt; IP and explore future projects.”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id="4euTZp"&gt;Microsoft had initially &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/24151047/xbox-shuts-down-arkane-austin-tango-gameworks-microsoft"&gt;announced in May that it was closing Tango Gameworks&lt;/a&gt;, alongside &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/23715862/redfall-review-xbox-pc"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Redfall&lt;/em&gt; developer Arkane Austin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;em&gt;Mighty Doom&lt;/em&gt; developer Alpha Dog Studios — three studios it inherited after acquiring ZeniMax in 2021. The impending Tango Gameworks closure was &lt;a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/Games/comments/1copkub/hifi_rush_gets_reverse_review_bombed_after/"&gt;widely criticized...&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;
    &lt;a href="https://www.theverge.com/2024/8/12/24218424/hifi-rush-studio-tango-gameworks-saved-krafton-microsoft"&gt;Continue reading&amp;hellip;&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/p&gt;

</content>
